approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `amount` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

returns._0: Amount of tokens that the sett can provide to the strategy.
Balance of token handled by the sett.

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals used to get its user representation. For example, if `decimals` equals `2`, a balance of `505` tokens should be displayed to a user as `5.05` (`505 / 10 ** 2`). Tokens usually opt for a value of 18, imitating the relationship between Ether and Wei. This is the value {ERC20} uses, unless this function is overridden; NOTE: This information is only used for _display_ purposes: it in no way affects any of the arithmetic of the contract, including {IERC20-balanceOf} and {IERC20-transfer}.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically decreases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address. - `spender` must have allowance for the caller of at least `subtractedValue`.

deposit(uint256).details: See `_depositFor` for details on how deposit is implemented.

deposit(uint256,bytes32[]).details: See `_depositForWithAuthorization` for details on guestlist authorization.

params.proof: Merkle proof to validate in the guestlist.

depositAll().details: See `_depositFor` for details on how deposit is implemented.

depositAll(bytes32[]).details: See `_depositForWithAuthorization` for details on guestlist authorization.

params.proof: Merkle proof to validate in the guestlist.

depositFor(address,uint256).details: See `_depositFor` for details on how deposit is implemented.

params._recipient: Address to issue the Sett shares to.

depositFor(address,uint256,bytes32[]).details: See `_depositForWithAuthorization` for details on guestlist authorization.

params._recipient: Address to issue the Sett shares to.

earn().details: Pause is enforced at the Strategy level (this allows to still earn yield when the Vault is paused)

params._token: Address of the token to be emitted.

getPricePerFullShare().details: Sett starts with a price per share of 1.

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically increases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

params._badgerTree: Address of badgerTree used for emissions.
params._feeConfig: Values for the 4 different types of fees charges by the sett         [performanceFeeGovernance, performanceFeeStrategist, withdrawToVault, managementFee]         Each fee should be less than the constant hard-caps defined above.
params._name: Specify a custom sett name. Leave empty for default value.
params._symbol: Specify a custom sett symbol. Leave empty for default value.
params._token: Address of the token that can be deposited into the sett.
params._treasury: Address to distribute governance fees/rewards to.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

reportAdditionalToken(address).details: This function is called after the strategy sends the additional tokens to the sett.      Pausing on this function happens at the strategy level.

params._token: Address of additional token harvested by the strategy.

reportHarvest(uint256).details: This implicitly trusts that the strategy reports the correct amount.      Pausing on this function happens at the strategy level.

params._harvestedAmount: Amount of underlying token harvested by the strategy.

setManagementFee(uint256).details: See `_handleFees` to see how the management fee is calculated.

setMaxManagementFee(uint256).details: The input `_fees` should be less than the `MANAGEMENT_FEE_HARD_CAP` hard-cap.

params._fees: The new maximum cap for management fee.

setMaxPerformanceFee(uint256).details: The input `_fees` should be less than the `PERFORMANCE_FEE_HARD_CAP` hard-cap.

params._fees: The new maximum cap for performance fee.

setMaxWithdrawalFee(uint256).details: The input `_fees` should be less than the `WITHDRAWAL_FEE_HARD_CAP` hard-cap.

params._fees: The new maximum cap for withdrawal fee.

setPerformanceFeeGovernance(uint256).details: See `reportHarvest` and `reportAdditionalToken` to see how performance fees are charged.

setPerformanceFeeStrategist(uint256).details: See `reportHarvest` and `reportAdditionalToken` to see how performance fees are charged.

setStrategy(address).details: This is a rug vector, pay extremely close attention to the next strategy being set.      Changing the strategy should happen only via timelock.      This function must not be callable when the sett is paused as this would force depositors into a strategy they may not want to use.

params._newToEarnBps: The new maximum cap for management fee.

setWithdrawalFee(uint256).details: See `_withdraw` to see how withdrawal fee is charged.

params._token: Address of the token to be swept.

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `amount`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `amount`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `amount`.

withdraw(uint256).details: See `_withdraw` for details on how withdrawals are processed.

withdrawAll().details: See `_withdraw` for details on how withdrawals are processed.

withdrawToVault().details: This calls `_withdrawAll` on the strategy and transfers the balance to the sett.

available().notice: Defines how much of the Setts' underlying is available for strategy to borrow.

balance().notice: Gives the total balance of the underlying token within the sett and strategy system.

deposit(uint256).notice: Deposits `_amount` tokens, issuing shares.         Note that deposits are not accepted when the Sett is paused or when `pausedDeposit` is true.

deposit(uint256,bytes32[]).notice: Deposits `_amount` tokens, issuing shares.         Checks the guestlist to verify that the calling account is authorized to make a deposit for the specified `_amount`.         Note that deposits are not accepted when the Sett is paused or when `pausedDeposit` is true.

depositAll().notice: Deposits all tokens, issuing shares.         Note that deposits are not accepted when the Sett is paused or when `pausedDeposit` is true.

depositAll(bytes32[]).notice: Deposits all tokens, issuing shares.         Checks the guestlist to verify that the calling is authorized to make a full deposit.         Note that deposits are not accepted when the Sett is paused or when `pausedDeposit` is true.

depositFor(address,uint256).notice: Deposits `_amount` tokens, issuing shares to `recipient`.         Note that deposits are not accepted when the Sett is paused or when `pausedDeposit` is true.

depositFor(address,uint256,bytes32[]).notice: Deposits `_amount` tokens, issuing shares to `recipient`.         Checks the guestlist to verify that `recipient` is authorized to make a deposit for the specified `_amount`.         Note that deposits are not accepted when the Sett is paused or when `pausedDeposit` is true.

earn().notice: Deposits the available balance of the underlying token into the strategy.         The strategy then uses the amount for yield-generating activities.         This can be called by either the keeper or governance.         Note that earn cannot be called when deposits are paused.

emitNonProtectedToken(address).notice: Sends balance of any extra token earned by the strategy (from airdrops, donations etc.)         to the badgerTree for emissions.         The `_token` should be different from any tokens managed by the strategy.         This can only be called by either strategist or governance.

getPricePerFullShare().notice: Gives the price for a single Sett share.

initialize(address,address,address,addre.notice: Initializes the Sett. Can only be called once, ideally when the contract is deployed.

pause().notice: Pauses everything.         This can be called by either guardian or governance.

pauseDeposits().notice: Pauses only deposits.         This can be called by either guardian or governance.

performanceFeeGovernance().notice: Fees ///all fees will be in bps

reportAdditionalToken(address).notice: Used by the strategy to report harvest of additional tokens to the sett.         Charges performance fees on the additional tokens and transfers fees to treasury and strategist.         The remaining amount is sent to badgerTree for emissions.         Updates harvest variables for on-chain APR tracking.         This can only be called by the strategy.

reportHarvest(uint256).notice: Used by the strategy to report a harvest to the sett.         Issues shares for the strategist and treasury based on the performance fees and harvested amount.         Issues shares for the treasury based on the management fee and the time elapsed since last harvest.         Updates harvest variables for on-chain APR tracking.         This can only be called by the strategy.

setGovernance(address).notice: Change governance addressCan only be changed by governance itself

setGuardian(address).notice: Changes the guardian address.         Guardian is an authorized actor that can pause the sett in case of an emergency.         This can only be called by governance.

setGuestList(address).notice: Changes the guestlist address.         The guestList is used to gate or limit deposits. If no guestlist is set then anyone can deposit any amount.         This can be called by either governance or strategist.         Note that this can only be called when the sett is not paused.

setKeeper(address).notice: Change keeper addressCan only be changed by governance itself

setManagementFee(uint256).notice: Sets the management fee taken by the treasury on the AUM in the sett.         The fee is calculated at the time of `reportHarvest` and is used to issue new shares for the treasury.         The new management fee should be less than `maxManagementFee`.         This can be called by either governance or strategist.

setMaxManagementFee(uint256).notice: Sets the max management fee that can be charged by the Sett.         This can only be called by governance.

setMaxPerformanceFee(uint256).notice: Sets the max performance fee that can be charged by the Sett.         This can only be called by governance.

setMaxWithdrawalFee(uint256).notice: Sets the max withdrawal fee that can be charged by the Sett.         This can only be called by governance.

setPerformanceFeeGovernance(uint256).notice: Sets the performance fee taken by the treasury on the harvests.         The fee is taken at the time of harvest reporting for both the underlying token and additional tokens.         For the underlying token, the fee is used to issue new shares for the treasury.         The new performance fee should be less than `maxPerformanceFee`.         This can be called by either governance or strategist.

setPerformanceFeeStrategist(uint256).notice: Sets the performance fee taken by the strategist on the harvests.         The fee is taken at the time of harvest reporting for both the underlying token and additional tokens.         For the underlying token, the fee is used to issue new shares for the strategist.         The new performance fee should be less than `maxPerformanceFee`.         This can be called by either governance or strategist.

setStrategist(address).notice: Change strategist addressCan only be changed by governance itself

setStrategy(address).notice: Changes the strategy address.         This can only be called by governance.         Note that this can only be called when sett is not paused.

setToEarnBps(uint256).notice: Sets the fraction of sett balance (in basis points) that the strategy can borrow.         This can be called by either governance or strategist.         Note that this can only be called when the sett is not paused.

setTreasury(address).notice: Changes the treasury address.         Treasury is recipient of management and governance performance fees.         This can only be called by governance.         Note that this can only be called when sett is not paused.

setVesting(address).notice: Changes the vesting contract address.         Vesting contract is used to vest withdrawn tokens linearly over period of 21 days         This can only be called by governance.

setWithdrawalFee(uint256).notice: Sets the withdrawal fee charged by the Sett.         The fee is taken at the time of withdrawals in the underlying token which is then used to issue new shares for the treasury.         The new withdrawal fee should be less than `maxWithdrawalFee`.         This can be called by either governance or strategist.

sweepExtraToken(address).notice: Sweeps the balance of an extra token from the vault and strategy and sends it to governance.         The `_token` should be different from any tokens managed by the strategy.         This can only be called by either strategist or governance.

unpause().notice: Unpauses everything         This can only be called by governance.

unpauseDeposits().notice: Unpauses deposits.         This can only be called by governance.

version().notice: Used to track the deployed version of the contract.

withdraw(uint256).notice: Redeems `_shares` for an appropriate amount of tokens.         Note that withdrawals are not processed when the Sett is paused.

withdrawAll().notice: Redeems all shares, issuing an appropriate amount of tokens.         Note that withdrawals are not processed when the Sett is paused.

withdrawToVault().notice: Withdraws all funds from the strategy back to the sett.         This can be called by either governance or strategist.
